Vheadline
p2
VThrilling concert by trio
p3
sVnews
p4
VMarking the 75th Jayanthi of Jayendra Saraswathi Swamy of Kanchi Kamakoti Peetham, the reputed Malladi trio &#8212; father Malladi Suribabu and sons Sriram Prasad and Ravikumar presented a vocal concert at Sri Kanchi Kamakoti Peethastha Chandramouliswara Swamy Devasthanam situated in Labbipet, Vijayawada.The trio started the concert withGajananayutham Ganeswaramin Chakravakam and followed it withParameswarain Nata andKanjadalayakshiin Kamala Manohari. Next, Sriram Prasad delineated in a detailed and attractive manner, the raga Anandabhairavi and the trio sang Syama Sastri&#8217;sMarivere gaticoncluding it with efficient kalpana swaras. Bhava laden and melodious passages found place in Pantuvarali in which father and sons rendered SivaSiva Siva Yanarada. Also good kalpana swaras adorned the keertana. In Kokilaravam, a rare raga, Malladis sangKodanda Rama. Ravi Kumar sang a sumptuous version of Sankarabharanam in which the trio renderedAkshaya Linga Vibhowith great bhava sense and crisp swara kalpana. Faithful and melodious support was given by Palaparthi Nageswara Rao, a seasoned violinist. N.S. Kalyanaraman and I. Anjaneya Sastri provided excellent support on the mridangam and ghatam respectively. Their tani was thrilling.
